{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17528264","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17528264"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:39:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:39:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14280"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14280","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14280"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.11,0.33,0.11,0.3]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6975"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68908"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6975","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6975"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14280"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54365"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"15"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"2132"},{"type":"tags","id":"2347"},{"type":"tags","id":"2918"},{"type":"tags","id":"4487"},{"type":"tags","id":"4534"},{"type":"tags","id":"4920"},{"type":"tags","id":"4921"},{"type":"tags","id":"4969"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"12756"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"16390"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27448"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43513"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44413"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45030"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68908","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/68908"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old Aboriginal male from East Arnhem Land is referred to Renal Clinic with a two-week history of swollen legs and frothy urine. He has a medical history of hypertension and takes irbesartan and amlodipine. On examination, he appears unwell. His pulse rate is 78/min, blood pressure 149/88 mmHg, respiratory rate 20/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. He has pitting oedema to the level of the groin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInvestigations reveal:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUrinalysis: 3+ protein\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESerum albumin: 20 g/L (35-50)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETotal cholesterol: 7.2 mmol/L (2.0-5.5)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESerum creatinine: 130 \u03bcmol/L (60-110)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERenal biopsy light microscopy: Focal segmental glomerulosclerosis (FSGS)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EElectron microscopy: Diffuse foot process effacement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe nephrologist recommends starting high-dose oral prednisolone.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following tests is LEAST important to check before initiating steroid therapy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hepatitis B serology","Latent tuberculosis testing","Strongyloides serology","HbA1c","Serum cortisol"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe population of the Top End of the Northern Territory has a high incidence of several infections. This is particularly pronounced in the immunosuppressed cohort e.g. patients on high-dose prednisolone \u0026gt;0.5mg/Kg/day for \u0026gt;14days, as well as patients undergoing chemotherapy or on other potent immunosuppressive agents.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EConditions such as disseminated strongyloidiasis, melioidosis, tuberculosis, scabies hyper-infestation and activation of hepatitis B virus infection can occur in immunosuppressed patients, and are generally more common in the Top End region compared to other parts of Australia. Hence, it is important to screen for such conditions prior to the commencement of high dose steroids.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatitis B serology\u003C/strong\u003E is crucial to check before starting immunosuppressive therapy, including steroids. Patients with chronic or occult hepatitis B infection are at risk of viral reactivation when immunosuppressed, which can lead to severe hepatitis and liver failure. This is particularly important in populations with a higher prevalence of hepatitis B.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELatent tuberculosis testing \u003C/strong\u003Eis essential to screen for latent tuberculosis infection. Steroid therapy can reactivate latent TB, leading to active disease. Identifying and treating latent TB before starting steroids is crucial to prevent this complication.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStrongyloides serology\u003C/strong\u003E screening is important in this patient from an endemic area. Disseminated strongyloidiasis can be life-threatening. Screening and treating for Strongyloides before starting steroids is standard practice in patients from endemic regions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHbA1c\u003C/strong\u003E (glycated haemoglobin) is important to check before starting steroid therapy. Steroids can cause or exacerbate hyperglycaemia, and knowing the baseline glycaemic status helps in monitoring and managing this side effect. This is particularly relevant in patients with risk factors for diabetes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Eserum cortisol\u003C/strong\u003E can be useful in some situations to assess adrenal function, it is not routinely necessary before starting exogenous steroid therapy for most patients. The other tests mentioned are more critical for patient safety when initiating immunosuppression.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn summary, when starting high-dose steroid therapy, priority should be given to screening for infections that can be reactivated (hepatitis B, tuberculosis, strongyloidiasis) and assessing baseline metabolic status (diabetes). These tests are crucial for preventing potentially severe complications of immunosuppressive therapy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The population of the Top End of the Northern Territory has a high incidence of several infections.","This is particularly pronounced in the immunosuppressed cohort e.g. patients on high-dose prednisolone \u003E0.5mg/Kg/day for \u003E14days, as well as patients undergoing chemotherapy or on other potent immunosuppressive agents.","Conditions such as disseminated strongyloidiasis, melioidosis, tuberculosis, scabies hyper-infestation and activation of hepatitis B virus infection can occur in immunosuppressed patients."],"references":["Davis J. Prevention of opportunistic infections in immunosuppressed patients in the tropical Top End of the Northern Territory of Australia. The Department of Health and Aged Care; 2003 Dec 3;27(4). Available at: https://www1.health.gov.au/internet/main/publishing.nsf/Content/cda-pubs-cdi-2003-cdi2704-htm-cdi2704s.htm"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54365"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14280"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54365","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/54365"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-10T16:54:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-24T20:25:13+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6975"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68908"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":n